description.narrative: (Lebanon): USAID will continue to fund scholarships to academically meritorious yet financially disadvantaged students through a $17.8 million cooperative agreement to the Lebanese American University (LAU) in September 2015. This funding will provide full scholarships to at least 174 students over the next eight years. The first cohort of 73 scholars was enrolled as of August 2016; another cohort of around 74 students is expected by September 2017. The USP VII is a continuation of a cooperative agreement awarded in 2015, and available money will incrementally fund the mechanism to continue the scholarship support. As directed by Congress, the expansion to include private schools is planned in the new scholarship mechanism that is being currently designed for award by September 2018. This program attributes to the higher education earmark and is directed by the Congress.
